Citrullus colocynthis

   [4618.jpg]
   Authority (L.) Schrader
   Family Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Violales:Cucurbitaceae
   Synonyms
   Common names colocynth, vine of Sodom, wild-gourd, egusi, bitter
   cucumber, bitter gourd, bitter apple, wild watermelon, colocinto,
   coloquintida, pepino amargo, Koloquint
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 4618

   Notes
   GROWING PERIOD
   Annual or perennial herbaceous vine.
   COMMON NAMES
   Colocynth.
   FURTHER INF
   Colocynth is native from India to tropical Africa. It is a highly
   xerophytic plant. Productivity is enhanced during dry, sunny periods
   and reduced during periods of excessive rainfall and high humidity

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   White F 1983 pp 219
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 276 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 12 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Purseglove J 1974 pp 102 [USE]

